thread.title_full: Deputies seeking man accused of robbing coin store at gunpoint | OregonLive.com

author: Everton Bailey Jr. | The Oregonian/OregonLive
title: Deputies seeking man accused of robbing coin store at gunpoint
text:
Clackamas County deputies are seeking the public's help to track down a man who robbed a Milwaukie-area coin store at gunpoint on Thursday.
The robbery was reported around 3:20 p.m. at Coins on the Boulevard, 16210 S.E. McLoughlin Blvd . No one was injured.
The suspect is described as having a medium build, wearing a dark-colored hooded sweatshirt with an Under Armour logo, a dark-colored baseball hat with a sticker on the bill and a black mask covering his face. He ran south towards Southeast Vineyard Road after leaving the store.
The sheriff's office asked anyone with information about this incident to contact them through their tip line at 503-723-4949.
